title: Big Black Dog
author: adriana
text: the big black dog swiftly slinks around.  he slowly,  but quietly,  melts into the shadows.  he emerges only to sing his song.  finally,  he approaches me among the many trees that encase us.  the black dog comes closer and closer until i feel his wet nose on my hand.  his luminous eyes meet mine and his tail begins to quiver.  in an instant,  i feel his tongue paint my face with long,  rough,  strokes.  he finishes his master piece and then settles on the grass.  my hands stroke his head as his nose nuzzles my legs.  the black dog rolls over,  gesturing for me to pet him.  following his lead,  my hands travel to his stomach and begin to rub gently.  we sit for a while,  absorbing the tranquility like two sponges.  suddenly,  a crashing noise slices through the silence.  the black dog breaks away from my hand and jerks upward.  he then bolts of towards the shadows,  just as swiftly and quietly as he had come.

title: The Foolishness Of Mankind
author: aimen
text: the chirrupping of birds,  the hum of the nightingale.  the squeaking of the squirrel,  and that child's wail. . .   the earth is becoming,  almost disastrous to live on.  no one is realizing,  that it was the same place we were born on.   it is being crahed to pieces,  the child's wail becomes louder.  the birds stop chirrupping,  the nightingale cannot be seen let alone be heard.   man is destroying everything,  from trees to himself.  man is hunting animals,  they are becoming extinct.   why can't he hear the child's cry? or the sound of the birds? the singing of the nightingale? or the squirrel?  it is because,  man was born free.  he had no limits,  nor any priorities.   man gained the trust of god,  he was bowed to.  but god made a mistake,  man is a foe.   man can never change,  he will remain the same.  the earth will cry,  he will not listen.   but man will pay,  for all its misdeeds.  man will apoligise,  as his eyes will dart towards heaven.   man will never know,  its future.  he will never know,  that the earth will one day hold court.   man will never realize,  that life was a joke.  but he does know,   how to laugh. . .

title: Friendship
author: allie
text: friendship        live by fun        not always by rules        laugh until you can't        love like nothing else matters           we have great times         and we may endure hardships         we break the chains of friendship          we remake them and add new links        we cry with each other        we laugh with each other        each day brings adventures;        why not explore them together          we've stuck by each other        whether at school or home        we build each other up        we break each other down        we can never stay mad         secrets can be passed        because we're always trusted        popularity doesn't matter        as long as we're together           smiles spread like wildfires        nothing can ruin our day        we share past, present and future          we heal the wounds,         and admire the battle scars        in the blackness of life        we will always come together         we stand up to our enemies       to kep each other safe       we'll stand strong       and maybe falter along the way            we include, because six is better       than five       we've built our friendship on solid       ground       no matter what happes,        we will always come back         no one can get past us       we keep watch over one another       without taking breaks       we have little time;       let's make the most of it

title: Clumsy Old Me
author: allison
text: the clumsy  old me  whoosh,  i flew past the horrible front office and ran into the counceler with her cup filled to the brim with instant coffee.  â“sorryâ”,  i blurted.   â“but,  this is my new dressâ” she sobbed.   before she finished i was already down to the third grade hall.   after i passed the third grade hall,  i passed the gloomy music room where i could hear them singing jingle bells when it was october.   finally,  i was to my boring classroom.   i put my hand on the cold silver door handle,  and opened it.    â“allison,  you are late again, â” barked miss perky.   i slumped down in my seat,  but i slumped down to much and fell out of my seat.   everybody laughed,  even my teacher.   it was just another day at williams elementary.   â“well,  its time for specialsâ” miss perky sighed.   â“allison, â” haley blurted,  â“we have p. e. â”  i didnâ’t answer.    as i slowly walked down the hall,  with my head hung low,  mark sped down the hall with a jam jar full of blue,  red,  and yellow marbles.   i decided to wave to my nerdy,  spelling freak,  friend,  but as i brought my hand back to the side of my thigh,  i slammed into the right bottom corner of the marble jar.   crash! the marble jar went flying and almost hit the light,  right smack in the middle of the hall,  but just came back down and hit steve simmons on the head.   â“oh noâ”,  i whispered.   steve just lay there on the green and pink carpet.   â“i am fineâ”,  he mumbled.   â“but mary,  you better not hit me in the head again. â”  â“you really did it this timeâ” haley sighed.   â“now he will be calling everyone the wrong name. â”  steve got up and started stamping around in circles saying, â” i see starsâ” over and over again.   finally we were at p. e. ,  it was my favorite place because i never crash into anybody or hit him or her in the head.   â“you kids better be careful because the janitors will be doing there every six week cleaningâ”,  miss p.  said on the little black microphone.   today we were going to jog around the gym to some old time music so we can be prepared for the one-mile run.   as the music began to play miss laho the janitor began to start a conversation with mr.  p.   miss lahoâ’s red-hot painted fingernails were lightly vibrating on the electric mop.   â“allisonâ”,  haley mumbled, â” is it suppose to do that?â”  â“haley,  watch out!â” my nerdy spelling freak,  friend shouted.   the electric mop had zoomed over the silver gray bucket of water and was heading straight for haley,  so i dove on it to try and make it turn back around.   my,  plan did not go as planned.   the mop still went straight and bonked haley.  â“no, â” i yelled.   it was heading for the stag.  slam!  it hit the stage and made and enormous hole in the back.   oh no!  p. e.  was no longer my favorite place.   for the rest of the day i grow out of my clumsy self and act like a normal human being until tomorrow when the horrible cycle of humiliation starts all over again.   but for now i can pretend that i am the most graceful creature to walk the halls of my elementary.    a girl can dream canâ’t she?

title: Thumb's Up
author: allison
text: a broken thumb is no fun,                             when you could be having fun in the sun.                            you could be playing all the sports you like,                                but no,  you had to be riding a dirt bike.                                   then you fall off and hit the ground,                               and for a second you canâ’t here a sound.                                             smashing your thumb,                                                    is also no fun.                                       everyone comes rushing over,                            now you are wishing you had a four-leaf clover.                                    then youâ’re going to get some ice,                                       and youâ’re not feeling very nice.                                        next you go to get an x-ray,                             and youâ’re wishing you donâ’t have to stay.                                               first,  he numbs it.                                            that didnâ’t hurt a bit.                                         next,  he gives you a shot,                                              you feel like a robot.                                  then,  he pulls your thumb into place,                                      while your staring off into space.                                                he puts on your cast,                                               which was very fast.                                         then we go to the x-ray room,                                                     and boom!                                        my thumb wasnâ’t into place,                                you shouldâ’ve seen the look on my face.                                    he hung my thumb from the ceiling,                                   and soon my arm had a tingly feeling.                                   now itâ’s time for a new cast to go on,                                              so i started to yawn.                                            then i got another x-ray,                                          this time i donâ’t have to stay.                                                as a month goes by,                                             i am still having a sigh.                                           at least i have no more cast,                                              for that was in the past.                                          now you think youâ’re all done,                                      but no,  you still canâ’t have any fun.                                         now you have to wear a splint,                                          and it always gets full of lint.                                            it is really starting to smell,                                        i smelled it once and i had to yell!                                       itâ’s almost time for me to wrap-up,                                          so just remember this one line:                                                thumbâ’s up!

text: what if the world didnâ’t fight,  countries showing all their might,  and conquering weak and strong alike.  what if war went on strike?  what if disease took a vacation,  from hitting any of those in creation,  the children and adults didnâ’t know this blight.  what if health was all a right?  what if kindness was open to all,  and meanness didnâ’t force its pall,  on anyone,  anywhere and all were so sweet,  what if cruelty we all could defeat?  what if the world had changed its game,  what if the world was out of its shame,  people and animals harmonious together,  what if the worldâ’s sins were light as a feather?  what if all of us would take responsibility,  for making the world a place of tranquility,  saying,  â“this is my world and it is yoursâ’ too, â” so letâ’s try to make the world perfect and new.

title: They Do Not Want To See
author: ally
text: they do not want to see,  the scream of sorrow that burns the face,  that is rubbed in with sting,  and hurts it with disgrace.  they do not want to see the greed,  that hunts the field in search of need.   the people avoid the poor soul held captive,  though they see they are not active.  they do not want to feel the guilt,  that pounds on them like drums,  afraid that all the horror,  will make them all feel numb.   they try to run,  they try to hide,  but,  they cannot fight what is inside.  they do not want to hear the cry,  that hurts them deeply when they try.   so,  come along and hear this song,  to find out what is right from wrong.  the long road will never end,  and this is what i know,  my friend.   the journey leads a peaceful way,  if you know yourself and have a say.  in how the world will soon describe,  its people caring,  side by side.

title: What I Thought
author: alura
text: in this world there are disappointments,  lies,  and broken hearts.  i thought i could change it.   i was wrong.   i thought people could change.  i thought wrong.   you could think you love someone,  and they loved you back; but no they didnâ’t! they donâ’t really care about you.  there are people who lie,  and then there are people that fall for those lies.  i fell head first into a lie that will never be forgiven.  i went through so much,  so much that it has marked me for life.  he said he will be here,  waiting for me.  and after i sought out my problem,  after i dealt with my problem,  after i took him back.  he broke me,  chewed me up and spat me out.  he waited for me,  and i ignored him.  i took him into my heart and he squashed from the inside out.  i thought he waited for me because he loved me; he truly,  truly loved me.  i was wrong.  i went through so much just to see that he was the one for me.  and it turns out he wasnâ’t.  no one is.  iâ’m stupid for believing someone wanted me.  some one cared for me.  some one loved me.  ha! yeah right,  well i was proven wrong.  again,  and again,  and again.  iâ’m numb,  i canâ’t feel anymore.  no more emotions,  no more pain,  just no more.  i live in a black void,  a void that was caused when my heart was broken for the last time.  iâ’m done! no more! no more pain,  no more hurt,  no more me! no more anything,  i want to feel nothing,  and i want to be nothing.  all i wanted was to feel what love was,  but no iâ’m not allowed.   if i try iâ’ll just end up like i am now.  loveless,  cold,  and lonely.  in my life thereâ’s been heartache,  and pain.  and i donâ’t want to face that pain again.  iâ’m being comforted constantly,  and i wish they would just leave me alone.   iâ’m tired of being cared for,  because no one really cares.  they just act like they do; they act as if oh thatâ’s too bad.  when they donâ’t know anything.  they donâ’t know how i feel.  they never will! what happened to me? i used to be happy,  and now…nothing.  a blank,  a blank now,  a blank past,  a blank future.

title: The Mouse That Sat Upon My Head
author: amanda
text: when i awoke one morning,  a mouse sat on my head.  i asked, ''what are you doing there?'' it looked at me and said,   ''i could not find a bathroom,  and i could not find a bed,  and so i took a potty break and slept upon your head.   then i went into the kitchen,  and i said to your mom,  'do you have a mouse-sized tux,  for i'm going to the prom. '  i'm sorry i must tell you this,  she said, ''please wear this hose. '' sadly,  i lost my temper,  and bit her on the nose.   right now,  she's downstairs,  screaming,  writhing on the kitchen floor.  i'm sorry that i did it,  sometimes i'm a wild boar.   i did not know what else to say,  and so i said, ''that's true.  and now my mom will be so mad,  she'll be coming after you. ''  she'll set traps for all your family,  and all of your friends,  and she'll keep trying to catch you,  even after her nose mends. ''  he replied, ''oh,  i'll be fine,  for i don't live near here.  as for my friends and famlily,  they really have no fear. ''  good-bye,  my friend.  i'll see you soon,   or at least that's what i hope.  as for your mother's bite,  just wash it with ivory soap.   and then he left,  just disappeared,  vanished into thin air,  and that's when i felt something  dripping out of my hair!

text: i peer at the fish in their tank,  swimming gracefully with a flip of their tails.  they chase each other,  embrace each other,   and have not a care in the world.   i peer at the fish in their tank,  gliding forcefully with a slip of their fins.  they race each other,  and disgrace each other,  and have not a care in the world.   i peer at the fish in their tank,  and wish,  for a fleeting second,  to be one of them.  i would chase,  embrace,  race,   and disgrace.  and have not a care in the world.   as i peer at the fish in their tank,  i wonder- maybe,  they are wishing to be me.

title: If You Can
author: amirrah
text: if you can live a day with dread,  and watch the ones you loved dead if you can sail the rough seas,  and come back with a bunch of fleas,  if you can get bit and not take the hit amongst the ones you love most.  if you can live a life with mistakes,  but still go high on the stakes.   if you can give away to needy,  but also be a little greedy,  if you can take the bait,  and leave with no hate.  if you can shine but not glow,  and dance around in the snow.  if you can make others feel right,  and let them shine bright.   if you treat each other kind,  then you'll be treated fine.  if you can be caring,   people can be caring.  if you can keep going when everyone stops,  and take that leap of faith with one single hop.   if you can win the best that life has in store,  you'll be the woman that the world will bow before.

title: The Music of the Woods
author: andre'
text: the moon shines its misty light ever so quiet and peaceful.  when suddenly a quiver in the bush,  and a ruffle in the tree,  out pops a dainty little wood spirit.  with smooth oak skin,  and a leaf over its face,  he takes out his little twig fiddle,  and begins to play.  the stick flute,  acorn drum,  leaf bass,  and grass trumpet are all members of the little band of plants.  and the forest is no longer quiet.  the soft hum coming from the little orchestra of the woods fills the air,  and is heard by all.  and they continued to play,  until dawn came.  the sun came up,  drenching the sky with a golden light.  the last song ended and the little wood spirits put their instruments away,  and left.  only to come back tomorrow,  after the gold sun sank down below the horizon.  and as they left,  the forest was once again quiet.

title: Calling of the Dead
author: andrea
text: across the street,     as we race from art,       as we pass the street,         i heard a noise.   from the graveyard,      my class and i stop,        we hear bag pipes.   as two men carry,    a coffin huge,     our class stops our running,        and take a moment to honor the dead person,            even though we know not their name.   we know how we'd feel if one more of our loved ones had died.     and as we honor this man's life,        we thought of those who died.   as we whisper about the deceeced,    we think of how we want to be burried.      i thought of being crusified,       my friends want the traditional dirt,         as we look back one last time,          before heading into the building,             we remember these pipes. . .  . . . as the call of the dead.    and next year when we wanna dare each other to enter the grave yard at midnight on halloween,  we will think about the calling of the dead.     bag pipes. . .       bag pipes,  hmmm. . . the calling of the dead- bag pipes. . .   and as i leave these thoughts to swirl and curl to dissapearence,  i think of bag pipes and the song they played. . .  the national anthem - the calling of the dead,  bag pipes.
